"Denier Van Der Gon H.A.C., Kropff M.J., Van Breemen N., Wassmann R., Lantin R.S., Aduna E., Corton T.M., Van Laar H.H.","Optimizing grain yields reduces CH4 emissions from rice paddy fields",2002,"Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences of the United States of America","99","19",,"12021","12024",,,10.1073/pnas.192276599,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0037125968&partnerID=40&md5=801b98a8b8475c4dd73bb7bb776cae53","Laboratory of Soil Science and Geology, Wageningen University, P.O. Box 37, 6700 AA Wageningen, Netherlands; Laboratory of Crop and Weed Ecology, Wageningen University, P.O. Box 430, 6700 AK Wageningen, Netherlands; Fraunhofer-Institut für Atmosphärische Umweltforschung, Kreuzeckbahnstrasse 19, D-82467 Garmisch-Partenkirchen, Germany; Soil and Water Sciences Division, International Rice Research Institute, MCPO 1271, P.O. Box 3127, Makati City, Philippines; Agronomy, Soils, and Plant Physiology Division, Philippine Rice Research Institute, Munoz, Nueva Ecija 3119, Philippines; TNO Institute of Environmental Sciences, Energy Research and Process Innovation, P.O. Box 342, 7300 AH Apeldoorn, Netherlands","Denier Van Der Gon, H.A.C., Laboratory of Soil Science and Geology, Wageningen University, P.O. Box 37, 6700 AA Wageningen, Netherlands, TNO Institute of Environmental Sciences, Energy Research and Process Innovation, P.O. Box 342, 7300 AH Apeldoorn, Netherlands; Kropff, M.J., Laboratory of Crop and Weed Ecology, Wageningen University, P.O. Box 430, 6700 AK Wageningen, Netherlands; Van Breemen, N., Laboratory of Soil Science and Geology, Wageningen University, P.O. Box 37, 6700 AA Wageningen, Netherlands; Wassmann, R., Fraunhofer-Institut für Atmosphärische Umweltforschung, Kreuzeckbahnstrasse 19, D-82467 Garmisch-Partenkirchen, Germany; Lantin, R.S., Soil and Water Sciences Division, International Rice Research Institute, MCPO 1271, P.O. Box 3127, Makati City, Philippines; Aduna, E., Soil and Water Sciences Division, International Rice Research Institute, MCPO 1271, P.O. Box 3127, Makati City, Philippines; Corton, T.M., Agronomy, Soils, and Plant Physiology Division, Philippine Rice Research Institute, Munoz, Nueva Ecija 3119, Philippines; Van Laar, H.H., Laboratory of Crop and Weed Ecology, Wageningen University, P.O. Box 430, 6700 AK Wageningen, Netherlands","Microbial production in anoxic wetland rice soils is a major source of atmospheric CH4, the most important non-CO2 greenhouse gas. Much higher CH4 emissions from well managed irrigated rice fields in the wet than in the dry season could not be explained by seasonal differences in temperature. We hypothesized that high CH4 emissions in the wet season are caused by low grain to biomass ratios. In a screenhouse experiment, removing spikelets to reduce the plants' capacity to store photosynthetically fixed C in grains increased CH4 emissions, presumably via extra C inputs to the soil. Unfavorable conditions for spikelet formation in the wet season may similarly explain high methane emissions. The observed relationship between reduced grain filling and CH4 emission provides opportunities to mitigate CH4 emissions by optimizing rice productivity.","C allocation in rice plants; Global warming; Greenhouse gas; Rice production","methane; article; biomass; carbon fixation; controlled study; grain; greenhouse effect; greenhouse gas; irrigation (agriculture); nonhuman; photosynthesis; priority journal; rice; seasonal variation; temperature; wetland; Agriculture; Air Pollutants; Atmosphere; Carbon; Greenhouse Effect; Methane; Models, Biological; Nitrogen; Oryza sativa; Photosynthesis; Seasons",,"Air Pollutants; Carbon, 7440-44-0; Methane, 74-82-8; Nitrogen, 7727-37-9",,,,"Lelieveld, J., Crutzen, P.J., Dentener, F.J., (1998) Tellus, 50 B, pp. 128-150; Houghton, J.T., Meira Filho, L.G., Bruce, J., Lee, H., Callander, B.A., Haites, E., Harris, N., Maskell, K., (1995) Climate Change 1994, , Cambridge Univ. Press, Cambridge, U.K; Schütz, H., Holzapfel-Pschorn, A., Conrad, H., Rennenberg, R., Seiler, W., (1989) J. Geophys. Res., 94 (16), pp. 405-416; Yagi, K., Minami, K., (1990) Soil Sci. Plant Nutr., 36, pp. 599-610; Cicerone, R.J., Shetter, J.D., (1981) J. Geophys. Res., 86, pp. 7203-7209; Sass, R.L., Fisher, F.M., Harcombe, P.A., Turner, F.T., (1990) Global Biogeochem. Cycles, 4, pp. 47-68; Sass, R.L., Fisher, F.M., Turner, F.T., Fund, M.F., (1991) Global Biogeochem. Cycles, 5, pp. 335-350; Wassmann, R., Wang, M.X., Shangguan, X.J., Xie, X.L., Shen, R.X., Wang, Y.S., Papen, H., Seiler, W., (1993) Geophys. Res. Lett., 20, pp. 2071-2074; Denier van der Gon, H.A.C., Neue, H.U., (1995) Global Biogeochem. Cycles, 9, pp. 11-22; Huang, Y., Sass, R.L., Fisher, F.M., (1998) Global Change Biol., 4, pp. 247-268; Bodegom, P.M., Van Wassmann, R., Corton, T.M., (2002) Global Biogeochem. Cycles, , in press; Wassmann, R., Lantin, R.S., Neue, H.-U., (2000) Nutrient Cycling in Agroecosystems, 58, pp. 1-394; Corton, T.M., Bajita, J.B., Grospe, F.S., Pamplona, R.R., Assis C.A., Jr., Wassmann, R., Lantin, R.S., Buendia, L.V., (2000) Nutrient Cycling in Agroecosystems, 58, pp. 37-53; Hansen, J., Sato, M., Ruedy, R., Lacis, A., Oinas, V., (2000) Proc. Natl. Acad. Sci. USA, 97, pp. 9875-9880; Minoda, T., Kimura, M., (1994) Geophys. Res. Lett., 21, pp. 2007-2010; Minoda, T., Kimura, M., (1996) J. Geophys. Res., 101, pp. 21091-21097; Huang, Y., Sass, R.L., Fisher, F.M., (1997) Global Change Biol., 3, pp. 491-500; Yoshida, S., (1981) Fundamentals of Rice Crop Science, , International Rice Research Institute, Los Baños, Philippines; Huang, Y., Sass, R.L., Fisher, F.M., (1997) Global Change Biol., 3, pp. 489-497; Cao, M.K., Dent, J.B., Heal, O.W., (1995) Global Biogeochem. Cycles, 9, pp. 183-195; Huang, Y., Sass, R.L., Fisher, F.M., (1998) Global Change Biol., 4, pp. 247-268; Cao, M.K., Gregson, K., Marshall, S., Dent, J.B., Heal, O.W., (1996) Chemosphere, 33, pp. 879-897; Denier van der Gon, H.A.C., (2000) Global Biogeochem. Cycles, 14, 